(26, 1, '2021-03-14 09:22:00', '2021-03-14 09:22:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How to make a press release? In which case to make a press release? This article provides you with a Word press release template.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The press release is an effective and free tool&nbsp;that makes it possible to reach journalists and bloggers on the occasion of the launch of a company or an association, a product launch or a particular event: commercial operation, new logo,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://animationmonster.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">custom animated video</a>, corporate&nbsp;communication. The main advantage of a press release is to develop the&nbsp;notoriety&nbsp;of the company by arousing the interest of future readers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Too little used by small businesses, the press release makes it possible to get in touch with&nbsp;influencers&nbsp;or&nbsp;opinion leaders&nbsp;by the simple communication of information.&nbsp;In the worst case, the information will not be taken back.&nbsp;But with a little luck, you will have significant benefits and that without having spent a penny.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To have a chance of being published, your press release must:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>be consistent with the type of content offered in the newspapers, blogs or magazines you are targeting,</li><li>present important information (event, novelty, innovation),</li><li>Be clear and attractive.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Here are 10 tips for a successful press release</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>10 tips for a successful press release.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How to make a press release?&nbsp;Here are 10 tips to succeed in this delicate exercise.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 1:</strong>&nbsp;Build a well-targeted list of journalists or influencers.&nbsp;Create an Excel table with three columns: media name (newspaper, magazine, and blog), contact name, and email address.&nbsp;The list can mix web and paper contacts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 2:</strong>&nbsp;Be concise.&nbsp;A press release of one A4 page is more than enough.&nbsp;It can include a photo.&nbsp;Stick to the basics: What is it?&nbsp;Where is it happening?&nbsp;What does it consist of?&nbsp;Who is behind it?&nbsp;Who to contact to find out more?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 3:</strong>&nbsp;Take care of the title of your press release.&nbsp;It is a key success factor.&nbsp;If your headline is appealing and it speaks to the reporter, you have a chance of getting published.&nbsp;The headline should adopt the tone of a newspaper article: both neutral and appealing or surprising.&nbsp;For example:&nbsp;Furniture Durand hires its hundredth employee.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 4:</strong>&nbsp;Take care of your hat (little text under the title).&nbsp;The hat goes into a bit of detail and makes the connection between the title and the content.&nbsp;It justifies the title and makes you want to read more.&nbsp;For example:&nbsp;The repositioning of the company on kitchen furniture has boosted activity and investments.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 5:</strong>&nbsp;Stay objective in your content.&nbsp;It is not a question here of adopting an advertising tone but of communicating neutral and explicit information, which can leave the field open to the interpretation of journalists.&nbsp;\"Your objective\" does not mean hollow or without relief: the information can (must) be highlighted.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 6:</strong>&nbsp;Keep the information as simple as possible.&nbsp;Be a teacher and put yourself in the shoes of a reader who has never heard of you.&nbsp;Ban technical terms and professional jargon.&nbsp;Tell yourself that if the journalist has the slightest doubt about the meaning of a term, he will prefer to abstain.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 7:</strong>&nbsp;Be comprehensive.&nbsp;Deliver all the important information on the press release, without the journalist having to contact you again<strong>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 8:</strong>&nbsp;Encourage you to go further.&nbsp;Provide your contact information: last name, first name, e-mail, telephone.&nbsp;Encourage visitors to visit your website.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 9:</strong>&nbsp;Use free online emailing software to send your press release.&nbsp;Among these software’s, let us quote three: Mail jet, Mail Chimp or SendInBlue.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tip # 10:</strong>&nbsp;Use&nbsp;a PR agency&nbsp;if publishing press releases becomes a real strategy for you.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A Word press release template.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We offers you to download an example of a Word press release that can be used for an event, a product launch, a business launch or association.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'A Word Press Release Template (and 10 Tips)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-word-press-release-template-and-10-tips', '', '', '2021-03-14 09:22:00', '2021-03-14 09:22:00', '', 0, 'http://localhost/iblogger/?p=26', 0, 'post', '', 0),
